Two important figures of merit for bolometer characterization are the TCR (temperature coefficient of resistance) and the voltage responsivity of the devices. The TCR is the relative change in resistance with temperature and is shown in Eq. 1. The voltage responsivity (Rv), shown in Eq. 1, is measured in VW−1, it is the ratio of the output voltage and the incident light flux.1Rv=ηαRIbGth(1+ω2τth2)0.5,\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
